'''''Ukamenia sapporensis''''' is a [[moth]] in the family [[Tortricidae]]. It was described by Matsumura in 1931. It is found in [[Japan]]<ref>[http://choreutidae.lifedesks.org/pages/621 choreutidae.lifedesks.org]</ref> (Hokkaido, Honshu) and the [[Russian Far East]].

The [[wingspan]] is 10.5-14.5&nbsp;mm. The ground colour of the forewings is dark grey with a rosy-red costal patch, a bluish metallic mark, a series of metallic spots and ochreous-brown streaks. The hindwings are brownish grey.

Larvae have been recorded feeding on ''[[Hamamelis japonica]]'', ''[[Vaccinium oldhami]]'', ''[[Quercus mongolica]]'' and ''[[Castanea crenata]]''.<ref>[http://ci.nii.ac.jp/naid/110007707778 Notes on "Simaethis" sapporensis MATSUMURA with Description of a New Genus of Olethreutinae, Tortricidae]</ref>

